<darkcolour>A6416E</darkcolour><section><title>Report Speech</title><sectiontitle>To talk about what someone said, use &lt;I&gt;say&lt;/I&gt; (+ &lt;I&gt;that&lt;/I&gt;) or &lt;I&gt;tell&lt;/I&gt; + person.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Pre-intGRAM_12_2_1.mp3</titlesound><text1></text1><sound1>Pre-intGRAM_12_2_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>She &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;said&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; that she was happy.</text1a><text2></text2><sound2>Pre-intGRAM_12_2_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>She &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;told us&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; that she was happy.</text2a><titlesound2>Pre-intGRAM_12_2_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Change the verb tense in reported statements. Present tense changes to past tense. Past/Present Perfect changes to Past Perfect.</sectiontitle2><text3>"I like swimming."</text3><sound3>Pre-intGRAM_12_2_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>He said he &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;liked&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; swimming.</text3a><text4>"I went to Vancouver."</text4><sound4>Pre-intGRAM_12_2_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>She told us she &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;had been&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; to Vancouver.</text4a></section><section><title>Report Speech</title><sectiontitle>Modal verbs change to their past form. &lt;I&gt;Will&lt;/I&gt; changes to &lt;I&gt;would&lt;/I&gt; and &lt;I&gt;can&lt;/I&gt; changes to &lt;I&gt;could&lt;/I&gt;.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Pre-intGRAM_12_2_7.mp3</titlesound><text1>"I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;will&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; watch the match."</text1><sound1>Pre-intGRAM_12_2_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>He said he &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;would&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; watch the match.</text1a><text2>"They &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;can&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; dance."</text2><sound2>Pre-intGRAM_12_2_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>She said they &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;could&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; dance.</text2a><titlesound2>Pre-intGRAM_12_2_10.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Change the pronoun if necessary.</sectiontitle2><text3>"He's &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;our&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; doctor."</text3><sound3>Pre-intGRAM_12_2_11.mp3</sound3><text3a>She said that he was &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;their&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; doctor.</text3a><text4>"I like &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;your&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; hat."</text4><sound4>Pre-intGRAM_12_2_12.mp3</sound4><text4a>She told me she liked &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;my&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; hat.</text4a></section></grammar>